          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Combine",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Combine the witch hazel, aloe vera gel, and vegetable glycerine in the bottle. Shake to mix -- the aloe gel will incorporate into the witch hazel. Add the essential oils, cap, and shake again. The product will have a slightly gel-like, cloudy appearance.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "How to use",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Shake before use. After shaving, rinse off any remaining shaving soap and pat the skin dry. Pour a small amount (about 5 ml, a teaspoon) into the palm and apply to the shaved area. The witch hazel will sting slightly on nicks or cuts -- this is normal. The sting subsides in 30 seconds. Do not apply to broken skin if sensitivity is a concern.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Storage and shelf life",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Keep at room temperature or in the refrigerator (the cool temperature feels soothing on application). Use within two months. Shake before each use. Discard if the liquid separates permanently or develops an off smell.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
